.TH PRIVACY-POOLS 1
.SH NAME
privacy-pools \- interact with Privacy Pools v1
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B privacy-pools
[options] [command]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Privacy Pools CLI provides public deposits, private relayed withdrawals, ragequit recovery, account sync, and agent\-friendly JSON discovery.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B init
Create, load, or finish setting up your Privacy Pools account
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools init [options]\fR
.TP
.B upgrade
Check for CLI updates
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools upgrade [options]\fR
.TP
.B config
View and manage CLI configuration
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools config [options]\fR
.TP
.B config list
List all configuration keys and their current values
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools config list [options]\fR
.TP
.B config get
Read a single configuration key
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools config get <key> [options]\fR
.TP
.B config set
Write a single configuration key
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools config set <key> [value] [options]\fR
.TP
.B config unset
Clear a single configuration key
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools config unset <key> [options]\fR
.TP
.B config path
Print the configuration directory path
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools config path [options]\fR
.TP
.B config profile
Manage named profiles
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools config profile [options]\fR
.TP
.B config profile list
List available profiles
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools config profile list [options]\fR
.TP
.B config profile create
Create a new named profile
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools config profile create <name> [options]\fR
.TP
.B config profile active
Show the currently active profile
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools config profile active [options]\fR
.TP
.B config profile use
Persist the active profile
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools config profile use <name> [options]\fR
.TP
.B flow
Deposit and privately withdraw in one guided workflow
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools flow [options]\fR
.TP
.B flow start
Deposit now and save a later private withdrawal workflow
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools flow start <amount> <asset> [options]\fR
.TP
.B flow watch
Resume a saved flow through funding, approval, privacy delay, and withdrawal
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools flow watch [workflowId|latest] [options]\fR
.TP
.B flow status
Show the saved easy\-path workflow state
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools flow status [workflowId|latest] [options]\fR
.TP
.B flow step
Advance a saved workflow by at most one unit of work
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools flow step [workflowId|latest] [options]\fR
.TP
.B flow ragequit
Recover a saved workflow publicly via ragequit
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools flow ragequit [workflowId|latest] [options]\fR
.TP
.B simulate
Preview deposit, withdraw, and ragequit without submitting
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools simulate [options]\fR
.TP
.B simulate deposit
Preview deposit validation without signing or submitting
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools simulate deposit <amount> [asset] [options]\fR
.TP
.B simulate withdraw
Preview withdrawal validation without signing or submitting
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools simulate withdraw [amount] [asset] [options]\fR
.TP
.B simulate ragequit
Preview ragequit validation without signing or submitting
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools simulate ragequit [asset] [options]\fR
.TP
.B pools
Browse available pools
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools pools [asset] [options]\fR
.TP
.B status
Check account setup and network status
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools status [options]\fR
.TP
.B tx\-status
Check async transaction submission status
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools tx\-status <submissionId> [options]\fR
.TP
.B activity
View recent deposits and withdrawals across pools
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools activity [asset] [options]\fR
.TP
.B protocol\-stats
View aggregate network statistics
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools protocol\-stats [options]\fR
.TP
.B pool\-stats
View statistics for one pool
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools pool\-stats [asset] [options]\fR
.TP
.B describe
Describe a command's flags, args, and output schema
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools describe [command] [options]\fR
.TP
.B explain
Explain a bundled JSON schema path
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools explain <schemaPath> [options]\fR
.TP
.B deposit
Deposit ETH or ERC\-20 tokens into a pool
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools deposit <amount> [asset] [options]\fR
.TP
.B withdraw
Withdraw privately from a pool
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools withdraw [amount] [asset] [options]\fR
.TP
.B withdraw quote
Request relayer quote and limits without generating a proof
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools withdraw quote <amountOrAsset> [amount] [options]\fR
.TP
.B broadcast
Broadcast a signed envelope or relayer request built elsewhere
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools broadcast <input> [options]\fR
.TP
.B accounts
View balances, approval status, and pool accounts
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools accounts [options]\fR
.TP
.B migrate
Check migration status for legacy pool accounts
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools migrate [options]\fR
.TP
.B migrate status
Check migration status for legacy pool accounts
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools migrate status [options]\fR
.TP
.B history
View your deposit and withdrawal history
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools history [options]\fR
.TP
.B sync
Sync account state with the latest onchain data
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools sync [asset] [options]\fR
.TP
.B ragequit
Recover funds publicly to your deposit address
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools ragequit [asset] [options]\fR
.TP
.B guide
Learn key concepts, workflows, and troubleshooting
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools guide [topic] [options]\fR
.TP
.B completion
Generate or install shell tab completion
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools completion [shell] [options]\fR
.TP
.B capabilities
Describe CLI capabilities for agents
.br
Usage: \fBprivacy\-pools capabilities [options]\fR
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-chain <name>
Target chain (mainnet, arbitrum, optimism, ...)
.TP
.B \-j, \-\-json
Machine\-readable JSON output on stdout. After the command name, pass \-\-json <fields> or \-\-json=<fields> to select top\-level fields.
.TP
.B \-\-template <template>
Render structured output through a lightweight Mustache\-style template with {{path.to.value}} placeholders and {{#items}}...{{/items}} list iteration
.TP
.B \-o, \-\-output <format>
Output format: table (default), csv, json, yaml, wide, name
.TP
.B \-y, \-\-yes
Skip confirmation prompts
.TP
.B \-\-web
Open the primary explorer or portal link in your browser when available
.TP
.B \-\-help\-brief
Show condensed command help without the extended guide appendix
.TP
.B \-r, \-\-rpc\-url <url>
Override RPC URL
.TP
.B \-\-agent
Machine\-friendly mode (alias for \-\-json \-\-yes \-\-quiet)
.TP
.B \-q, \-\-quiet
Suppress human\-oriented stderr output
.TP
.B \-\-no\-banner
Disable ASCII banner output
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Enable verbose/debug output (\-v info, \-vv debug, \-vvv trace)
.TP
.B \-\-no\-progress
Suppress spinners/progress indicators (useful in CI)
.TP
.B \-\-no\-header
Suppress header rows in CSV and wide/tabular table output
.TP
.B \-\-timeout <seconds>
Network/transaction timeout in seconds (default: 30)
.TP
.B \-\-jmes <expression>
Filter JSON output with a JMESPath expression (implies \-\-json)
.TP
.B \-\-jq <expression>
Compatibility alias for \-\-jmes (JMESPath, not jq syntax)
.TP
.B \-\-no\-color
Disable colored output (also respects NO_COLOR env var)
.TP
.B \-\-profile <name>
Use a named profile (separate wallet identity and config)
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PRIVACY_POOLS_HOME, PRIVACY_POOLS_CONFIG_DIR
Override the CLI config directory.
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Fallback config base used as $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/privacy-pools when no Privacy Pools override is set and no legacy ~/.privacy-pools directory exists.
.TP
.B PRIVACY_POOLS_PRIVATE_KEY
Signer private key. Takes precedence over the saved .signer file.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.privacy-pools/
Default configuration directory, unless an override or eligible XDG fallback is used.
.SH SEE ALSO
privacy-pools guide, privacy-pools capabilities, privacy-pools describe
